episode: I had a meeting with my boss' boss the other day and my preparation paid off!

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: Taking time to prepare is worth it.  I was asked to give an update to my manager's manager last week and I spent hours preparing and it went amazingly well.

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: That's fantastic! Your hard work really paid off.

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: Absolutely.  I don't get in front of that level of leadership very often and I was able to make a good impression.

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: Well done! That's a big achievement.

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: But now I've set the bar and have to do the same every time.

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: You've got this!

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: Yes, it just takes time away from getting work done.

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: I understand. Balancing is tough.

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: It really is.  In general what's important to me is getting good work done, not showing it off.

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: That makes sense. Your dedication shows.

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: I wish self promotion weren't necessary.

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: I get that.

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: How do you know you haven't overprepared?

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: Trust your instincts and the feedback you get.

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: Is there anything more objective?

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: Set clear goals and timelines.

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: I always make sure to do that.

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: Great strategy!

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: I also write down everything I want to say in meetings where I think I might get nervous and have my mind go blank.

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: Smart move!
